Description: Sinte aelwaer; a woman riding a donkey (allegory of quarrelsomeness), to left; she carries a pig under her arm; a cat perches on her hand and a bird sits on her head Woodcut
Producer name: Print made by: Cornelis Anthonisz. Theunissen
Curator's comments: The print in its complete form is accompanied by letterpress text and a title: 'Elck dient sinte aelwaer met grooter begheert die van veel menschen wort gheet'. The donkey derives from a print by Dürer of the Flight into Egypt (Bartsch 89).
